WEBVTT

00:01.131 --> 00:01.262
.

00:04.526 --> 00:07.790
[dramatic music]

00:07.833 --> 00:09.357
- That plane came through
the same light we did.

00:09.400 --> 00:11.489
Whoever was flying might be
able to get us out of here.

00:11.533 --> 00:12.664
- Levi?

00:12.708 --> 00:14.840
- Gavin knows about us.

00:14.884 --> 00:16.190
- Scott deserves the credit.

00:16.233 --> 00:18.148
I would've never thought
to use the heroin.

00:18.192 --> 00:19.454
- I was wrong. It's Lucas's.

00:19.497 --> 00:20.498
- If you don't give it to me
when we get back,

00:20.542 --> 00:21.673
I will kill you.

00:21.717 --> 00:22.718
- Maybe she can help.

00:22.761 --> 00:24.502
Says her name's
Rebecca Aldridge.

00:24.546 --> 00:26.156
- If there's another way to get
to Eve and Josh,

00:26.200 --> 00:28.376
you need to tell us.

00:28.419 --> 00:30.421
- This is the plane Levi flew.

00:30.465 --> 00:31.683
- [screams]

00:31.727 --> 00:33.511
- I'm pretty certain
he was electrocuted.

00:33.555 --> 00:35.035
- How is that possible?

00:35.078 --> 00:36.819
- There's only one person
who knows the answer to that.

00:36.862 --> 00:38.777
- What are you doing?
- There was an old man.

00:38.821 --> 00:42.216
He had something on his back,
a handprint.

00:42.259 --> 00:43.521
- Maybe someone's out there.

00:43.565 --> 00:45.219
Somebody who could help
get us home.

00:47.134 --> 00:50.093
[suspenseful music]

00:50.137 --> 00:56.752
♪

00:57.796 --> 00:59.581
- Who built this place?

01:05.326 --> 01:06.675
- Before the Europeans invaded,

01:06.718 --> 01:09.199
this area was inhabited
by native Californians.

01:09.243 --> 01:10.505
The Tongva, to be exact.

01:10.548 --> 01:13.290
- Well, it doesn't look
like they're home.

01:13.334 --> 01:15.118
There's no one even guarding
the entrance.

01:15.162 --> 01:17.338
- The Tongva were
a peaceful people.

01:17.381 --> 01:20.602
Probably don't have too
many enemies to worry about.

01:20.645 --> 01:22.778
- Then why build a wall?

01:22.821 --> 01:24.606
- Right now all that matters
is that my plane's

01:24.649 --> 01:27.522
picking up a signal,
and this is where it came from.

01:27.565 --> 01:29.176
We need to find
whoever sent it.

01:29.219 --> 01:30.655
Maybe they can help us
repair the plane.

01:30.699 --> 01:32.135
Hey, we're going to
split up into pairs.

01:32.179 --> 01:33.441
Meet back here in 15.

01:33.484 --> 01:35.312
- Wait, hold on,
hold on, hold on.

01:35.356 --> 01:38.750
I don't know about that.
We're intruding on their land.

01:38.794 --> 01:40.143
- I don't think we have
another option

01:40.187 --> 01:42.232
if we want to get out of here.

01:42.276 --> 01:43.668
You're with me.

01:43.712 --> 01:45.757
- Bro time. Cool.

01:47.672 --> 01:51.154
- Come on, let's go.
- Josh.

01:51.198 --> 01:53.504
You're coming with me.
- Mom--

01:53.548 --> 01:55.245
- You were attacked
by a wolf five days ago.

01:55.289 --> 01:56.420
- I feel fine.

01:56.464 --> 01:59.206
Besides,
I got the doctor with me.

01:59.249 --> 02:00.598
See you in 15 minutes.

02:02.861 --> 02:05.429
- Sooner we get going,
sooner we get out of here.

02:05.473 --> 02:12.480
♪

02:16.310 --> 02:18.747
- We searched the woods
for the man Lilly saw,

02:18.790 --> 02:19.922
but there's no sign of him.

02:19.965 --> 02:21.924
- Did he say anything to you?

02:21.967 --> 02:24.187
- Lilly told us
everything she knows.

02:24.231 --> 02:25.580
- Well, we have
to do something.

02:25.623 --> 02:27.147
- Yeah.

02:27.190 --> 02:29.192
Otherwise, we're all gonna
end up just like that dead guy.

02:29.236 --> 02:30.367
- You realize he had
a name, right?

02:30.411 --> 02:31.368
It was Eddie.

02:31.412 --> 02:32.804
- Yeah, whatever.
- Whatever?

02:32.848 --> 02:34.545
- Hey, we got plenty
to worry about

02:34.589 --> 02:36.939
without turning on each other,
okay?

02:36.982 --> 02:38.767
- I'm going to get back
to work on the Jeep.

02:38.810 --> 02:41.465
[apprehensive music]

02:41.509 --> 02:48.516
♪

02:50.779 --> 02:51.954
- You think there's
something more Lilly

02:51.997 --> 02:54.261
hasn't told us about that man?

02:54.304 --> 02:56.306
- Yeah, I do.

02:56.350 --> 02:58.482
- Got the same feeling myself.

02:58.526 --> 03:01.833
- If you want kids to open up,
you need to earn their trust.

03:01.877 --> 03:03.574
In my sessions,
I'd use board games,

03:03.618 --> 03:06.664
Legos, that kind of thing
to get them to relax.

03:06.708 --> 03:08.623
- Would softball work?

03:08.666 --> 03:10.538
- You bring a bat and ball
down here, doc?

03:10.581 --> 03:12.670
- No, but I've looked at most
of the vehicles

03:12.714 --> 03:14.368
in the clearing,
and the other day,

03:14.411 --> 03:16.587
I found one with a whole team's
worth of soft ball equipment.

03:16.631 --> 03:18.633
- You know,
it might not be a bad idea.

03:18.676 --> 03:25.683
♪

03:28.338 --> 03:29.513
- Doesn't seem like
there'd be a signal

03:29.557 --> 03:31.863
coming from in here.

03:31.907 --> 03:33.604
- Doesn't look that way.

03:38.305 --> 03:39.480
- Josh.

03:39.523 --> 03:42.265
Josh, there's food in here.
Oh, my God.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.832
- Wait, you don't know
if that's safe to eat.

03:43.875 --> 03:46.008
- I'm starving.
I'll take my chances.

03:46.051 --> 03:47.009
- I don't know
who's in more danger,

03:47.052 --> 03:48.619
You or Scott.

03:48.663 --> 03:49.925
- I'm fine.

03:49.968 --> 03:52.449
Lucas isn't actually
gonna kill Scott.

03:52.493 --> 03:53.711
He comes off a little
aggressive,

03:53.755 --> 03:55.278
but I think he's
actually harmless.

03:55.322 --> 03:58.977
- A drug dealer with a gun?
Yeah, sounds harmless to me.

03:59.021 --> 04:02.285
- All I know is he saved
my dad's life, okay?

04:02.329 --> 04:03.417
- I don't trust him.

04:03.460 --> 04:04.766
And I don't think
you should, either.

04:08.117 --> 04:11.773
- Hold on, are you jealous?
- What? No.

04:13.862 --> 04:16.386
- Okay. If you say so.

04:16.430 --> 04:17.909
- Get over yourself.

04:20.608 --> 04:23.828
- Look, Josh.
You're a really nice guy.

04:23.872 --> 04:25.830
I like you, just not like that.

04:25.874 --> 04:27.310
You know,
you're in high school.

04:27.354 --> 04:29.051
We're a life-stage apart.

04:29.094 --> 04:30.879
- Whatever.

04:34.012 --> 04:36.928
- There's no one here.
Maybe your radar got it wrong.

04:36.972 --> 04:38.408
- No, we just need
to keep looking.

04:38.452 --> 04:40.018
- Fine.

04:40.062 --> 04:42.456
- Eve. Eve.

04:43.979 --> 04:46.721
I am sorry
Gavin knows about us.

04:46.764 --> 04:47.939
Will you just talk to me,
please?

04:47.983 --> 04:50.507
- I don't know
what to say to you, Levi.

04:50.551 --> 04:52.596
I hate that
he found out that way.

04:52.640 --> 04:53.989
It should have been me.

04:54.032 --> 04:55.643
I should have been the one
to tell him.

05:00.691 --> 05:02.606
- What is it?

05:02.650 --> 05:05.392
[foreboding music]

05:05.435 --> 05:08.830
- That handprint.
I've seen it before.

05:08.873 --> 05:15.880
♪

05:21.103 --> 05:23.061
What is this place?

05:27.762 --> 05:29.329
[gasps]
Levi.

05:36.510 --> 05:37.946
What happened to him?

05:39.861 --> 05:41.689
- I don't know.

05:50.959 --> 05:53.440
- What's with the photo?
Levi, what's going on?

05:55.659 --> 05:58.401
- There's more
to my mission, Eve.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.576
More than just
saving the people

05:59.620 --> 06:01.926
who fell
in the La Brea sinkhole.

06:01.970 --> 06:03.363
- I don't understand.

06:06.540 --> 06:10.544
- I was also sent here to find
this man and seven others.

06:12.850 --> 06:15.853
- Why didn't you tell me this?
- Because it's classified.

06:15.897 --> 06:17.507
- Classified?

06:17.551 --> 06:20.597
We're way past
classified, Levi.

06:20.641 --> 06:22.599
Who is this guy?

06:22.643 --> 06:24.688
- Three years ago,

06:24.732 --> 06:27.082
another sinkhole
in the Mojave Desert opened up.

06:27.125 --> 06:29.432
An exploratory crew
was sent down,

06:29.476 --> 06:31.391
but they never made it back.

06:33.088 --> 06:34.785
He was one of the scientists
on the team.

06:40.051 --> 06:42.532
It's a long range
walkie-talkie.

06:42.576 --> 06:44.578
Solar-powered, thankfully.

06:44.621 --> 06:46.144
This is what my radar
was picking up.

06:46.188 --> 06:47.711
It belonged to him.

06:47.755 --> 06:49.626
- So you knew exactly what
the signal was the whole time.

06:49.670 --> 06:52.455
- These people fell through
the Mojave sinkhole.

06:52.499 --> 06:54.196
I had no reason to believe
they'd be in LA.

06:54.239 --> 06:56.154
[crackling]

07:04.946 --> 07:07.470
- This fire wasn't put out
very long ago.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.124
We're not alone.

07:09.167 --> 07:12.257
We need to find everyone else
and get the hell out of here.

07:12.301 --> 07:15.260
[dramatic music]

07:15.304 --> 07:16.958
♪

07:20.657 --> 07:21.092
.

07:21.136 --> 07:24.356
- You want me to fly?

07:24.400 --> 07:26.924
- You came here looking
for a way to save your family.

07:26.968 --> 07:28.404
This is it.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.319
[suspenseful music]

07:30.362 --> 07:33.017
- When do we leave?
- Tonight.

07:33.061 --> 07:34.149
- Hold on, tonight?

07:34.192 --> 07:36.456
- I realize the timing
is not ideal,

07:36.499 --> 07:40.242
but the plane's ready to go.
There's no need to wait.

07:40.285 --> 07:42.331
- But Dad, you never said
anything

07:42.374 --> 07:44.202
about flying down there
yourself.

07:44.246 --> 07:48.032
- Iz, I wish there was
another way.

07:48.076 --> 07:50.513
This might be our only chance
to get Mom and Josh back.

07:50.557 --> 07:52.036
- And what if none of you
come back?

07:52.080 --> 07:56.040
- The plane is safe.
Your father will make it.

07:56.084 --> 07:57.738
- What about Markman?

07:57.781 --> 08:01.393
He's not just gonna
let us fly down there.

08:01.437 --> 08:04.222
- I'll handle Markman.
I'm headed back to LA now.

08:04.266 --> 08:05.397
- Why?

08:05.441 --> 08:06.877
- The radar
at the Air Force base

08:06.921 --> 08:08.966
needs to be offline for you
to fly into the sinkhole.

08:09.010 --> 08:10.402
Now, I still have access
to the servers,

08:10.446 --> 08:12.448
but I need to be onsite
to shut it off.

08:12.492 --> 08:14.537
- Why are you doing this?

08:14.581 --> 08:17.671
If you get caught,
you'll go to prison.

08:17.714 --> 08:19.281
- You're not the only one
with people

08:19.324 --> 08:20.587
that you care about down there.

08:22.589 --> 08:25.287
- You lost someone
in the sinkhole too?

08:25.330 --> 08:28.116
- Not this sinkhole.

08:28.159 --> 08:31.554
This is Diana.
She's an engineer.

08:31.598 --> 08:34.383
Part of the team that went
into the Mojave sinkhole.

08:35.819 --> 08:39.736
She is my fiancée.

08:39.780 --> 08:42.565
She's been gone three years.

08:42.609 --> 08:44.524
- I'm sorry.

08:44.567 --> 08:46.569
- Yeah.

08:46.613 --> 08:50.312
I should go. Good luck.

08:50.355 --> 08:52.706
- Well, if we're gonna
leave tonight,

08:52.749 --> 08:55.099
we've got a lot of work to do.

08:55.143 --> 08:56.492
What do you say?

08:58.538 --> 09:00.714
- What's your plan?

09:00.757 --> 09:03.717
[foreboding music]

09:03.760 --> 09:05.501
♪

09:05.545 --> 09:08.635
- Josh, Riley.

09:12.508 --> 09:14.684
- Nothing.
- This place is huge.

09:17.469 --> 09:19.515
Levi, look at that.

09:19.559 --> 09:20.951
- It's a lookout post.

09:20.995 --> 09:22.300
- Yeah, we could see
the whole fort from up there.

09:22.344 --> 09:23.693
- Come on

09:27.697 --> 09:29.699
- Look at this.

09:29.743 --> 09:31.745
Come on.
Let's see where it goes.

09:31.788 --> 09:33.181
- Whoa, whoa, hold on, wait.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.357
A dark scary stairwell
underneath an ancient fort?

09:35.400 --> 09:38.055
I'll pass.
- Fine by me.

09:38.099 --> 09:39.230
- What--

09:55.246 --> 09:56.421
- Let me try to open it.

09:56.465 --> 09:57.640
- Maybe we shouldn't.

09:57.684 --> 10:04.429
♪

10:07.607 --> 10:09.870
- Great.
It leads outside the fort.

10:09.913 --> 10:11.306
Can we go back now?

10:14.570 --> 10:16.616
No. No.

10:20.532 --> 10:23.623
Well done, Josh. Truly.

10:33.371 --> 10:34.372
- Sick.

10:38.638 --> 10:42.816
Hey, we oughta take a couple
of these back to the clearing.

10:42.859 --> 10:44.818
- Or we could just
take one back home

10:44.861 --> 10:47.298
and sell it to a museum
for, like, a fortune.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.911
- I got 250k worth of heroin
back at camp.

10:50.954 --> 10:53.740
So I'm going to be just fine
when I get home.

10:53.783 --> 10:56.133
- [chuckles]
Of course.

10:57.395 --> 10:58.788
Good point.

11:00.747 --> 11:02.618
- Where did you hide it anyway?

11:02.662 --> 11:06.491
- Oh, you know, in the woods.

11:06.535 --> 11:08.493
- Where in the woods?

11:09.930 --> 11:11.235
- Well.

11:11.279 --> 11:13.890
First you leave the clearing,
and you had 100,

11:13.934 --> 11:16.806
120 meters or so
till you hit a stream,

11:16.850 --> 11:20.767
then you walk 50 steps
to your west

11:20.810 --> 11:23.465
and turn to your east
and, uh--

11:23.508 --> 11:25.206
ooh, shiny.

11:26.686 --> 11:28.775
- You have no idea
where you put it.

11:28.818 --> 11:30.646
- Well, did I say that?

11:30.690 --> 11:33.301
Because if I did, that was not
my intention at all.

11:33.344 --> 11:34.563
- You son of a bitch.

11:34.606 --> 11:35.956
- I can tell
that you're angry.

11:35.999 --> 11:37.348
- Oh, can you?

11:37.392 --> 11:41.309
[tense music]

11:41.352 --> 11:42.789
- Jesus, calm down.

11:42.832 --> 11:49.839
♪

11:57.804 --> 12:00.763
Scott, pick up the gun.

12:00.807 --> 12:02.243
Pick up the gun and shoot him.

12:02.286 --> 12:05.942
Pick up the gun.
Pick up the gun.

12:05.986 --> 12:07.857
- Whoa, whoa, watch out.

12:10.904 --> 12:12.993
- Don't move.

12:13.036 --> 12:15.604
- You speak English?

12:15.647 --> 12:17.562
That's entirely unexpected.

12:26.049 --> 12:26.267
.

12:26.310 --> 12:27.790
- Hey, Lilly.

12:27.834 --> 12:29.487
Softball game's about to start.

12:29.531 --> 12:31.141
Wanna play?

12:31.185 --> 12:33.796
- She's fine. Thanks.

12:33.840 --> 12:36.016
- I think we both know
Lilly can speak for herself.

12:38.496 --> 12:41.804
- I'd like to, if that's okay.

12:44.459 --> 12:47.070
- Great. Go warm up.

12:52.859 --> 12:55.339
- Look, I know I owe you
an explanation.

12:55.383 --> 12:57.733
- I'm listening.

12:57.777 --> 13:02.825
- My father was a good man,
a God-fearing man,

13:02.869 --> 13:04.827
but strict.

13:04.871 --> 13:07.917
He didn't trust
the outside world.

13:07.961 --> 13:10.224
And then we got down here.

13:10.267 --> 13:13.749
He said we needed to stay away
from all of you,

13:13.793 --> 13:16.056
to rely only on ourselves.

13:16.099 --> 13:18.275
- He told Lilly
not to talk to us.

13:20.277 --> 13:22.149
- I was just doing
what he wanted.

13:22.192 --> 13:24.020
- I understand, I do.

13:24.064 --> 13:28.024
But we are all
in this together now.

13:28.068 --> 13:31.419
You have to be honest with us
from here on out.

13:31.462 --> 13:32.768
- I will.

13:35.075 --> 13:38.382
- Did Lilly say anything else
about the man she saw?

13:38.426 --> 13:41.864
- No.
- You sure?

13:41.908 --> 13:44.214
It felt like there
was something more,

13:44.258 --> 13:45.868
something
she was afraid to tell us?

13:45.912 --> 13:47.870
- No, sorry.

13:47.914 --> 13:52.048
If she says anything else,
I'll let you know.

13:52.092 --> 13:54.224
- Okay, thank you.

13:54.268 --> 13:57.227
[apprehensive music]

13:57.271 --> 14:00.883
♪

14:00.927 --> 14:01.971
- I don't see anyone.

14:02.015 --> 14:03.451
- Just give it another minute.

14:03.494 --> 14:04.495
- Mom!

14:06.584 --> 14:07.934
- Josh?

14:07.977 --> 14:10.327
What are you doing out there?

14:10.371 --> 14:12.808
- Long story.
- Okay. Well, stay there.

14:12.852 --> 14:13.896
We're gonna go
find Scott and Lucas,

14:13.940 --> 14:15.245
and we'll come to you.

14:15.289 --> 14:16.420
- Eve, look.

14:16.464 --> 14:19.423
[foreboding music]

14:19.467 --> 14:24.254
♪

14:24.298 --> 14:25.821
- Who are they?

14:28.868 --> 14:31.435
- Riley, Josh, run.

14:31.479 --> 14:33.046
- Go, go.

14:33.089 --> 14:34.961
[warriors shouting]

14:35.004 --> 14:35.962
[horn blares]

14:36.005 --> 14:37.964
- Come on.

14:38.007 --> 14:39.835
Go! Go!

14:39.879 --> 14:43.143
[horn blaring]

14:47.103 --> 14:49.062
- Eve, we can't go this way.
- I have to get to Josh.

14:49.105 --> 14:51.020
- We can't. We have to go now.

14:51.064 --> 14:52.326
Come on.

14:56.504 --> 14:59.202
- Come on. Come on.

14:59.246 --> 15:02.379
[grunting, panting]

15:02.423 --> 15:03.424
- [gasps]

15:03.467 --> 15:06.340
[coughing]

15:08.385 --> 15:09.952
[groans]

15:09.996 --> 15:11.127
- Good, you're awake.

15:11.171 --> 15:13.303
[unnerving music]

15:13.347 --> 15:15.958
- Where are we?

15:16.002 --> 15:17.481
- Some weird temple, I think.

15:17.525 --> 15:19.135
Oh, and not to alarm you,

15:19.179 --> 15:21.224
but there's
a dead guy over there.

15:23.183 --> 15:26.012
- Oh, Jesus.
- Yeah.

15:27.665 --> 15:29.058
- Who are these people?

15:29.102 --> 15:30.233
- That is a good question

15:30.277 --> 15:31.974
because I have
no freaking idea anymore.

15:32.018 --> 15:33.454
- Oh, I thought
you were the expert.

15:33.497 --> 15:34.977
- Yeah, so did I,

15:35.021 --> 15:36.326
until we were attacked
by two white guys

15:36.370 --> 15:39.068
who speak English
who definitely weren't Tongva.

15:39.112 --> 15:40.635
Whoever they are,
they're incredibly adept

15:40.678 --> 15:41.984
at tying knots.

15:42.028 --> 15:44.160
- Oh, yeah, well,
we wouldn't be tied up

15:44.204 --> 15:47.033
if you would just
grabbed my gun like I told you.

15:47.076 --> 15:49.035
- I froze.
What was I supposed to do?

15:49.078 --> 15:50.514
- I don't know.
Not be a little bitch.

15:50.558 --> 15:51.994
- What the hell does it
even mean?

15:52.038 --> 15:53.517
- Hey, shut up, shut up.

15:53.561 --> 15:56.956
[indistinct voices, footsteps]

15:59.045 --> 16:01.003
- [sighs]
- Oh, man.

16:01.047 --> 16:05.094
- Okay, we need to get out of
here before we end up like him.

16:07.053 --> 16:10.926
[suspenseful music]

16:10.970 --> 16:13.450
- There's gotta be
another way out of here.

16:13.494 --> 16:16.062
- They're coming.
We need to hide. In here.

16:16.105 --> 16:20.022
♪

16:20.066 --> 16:23.243
[indistinct voices]

16:28.422 --> 16:30.076
- Hello.

16:32.426 --> 16:33.557
- I don't think
they understand.

16:33.601 --> 16:36.560
- They understand a smile,
don't they?

16:36.604 --> 16:38.345
It's best if they think
we're friendly.

16:38.388 --> 16:40.956
- It's not working.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.002
Okay. Change of plans.

16:43.045 --> 16:45.221
We gotta get out of here
before they give us up.

16:45.265 --> 16:48.007
[indistinct shouting]

16:51.445 --> 16:52.489
- It's too late for that.

16:54.622 --> 16:56.580
- In there. Go, go, go, go, go.

17:03.457 --> 17:05.067
- It's a dead end.

17:05.111 --> 17:11.987
♪

17:36.794 --> 17:40.320
[horn blaring]

17:48.110 --> 17:49.416
Do you think they're gone?

17:51.157 --> 17:52.332
- Yeah.

17:52.375 --> 17:54.116
I think they're
going back to the fort.

17:54.160 --> 17:57.119
- Good. Then we're safe here.
- No.

17:57.163 --> 17:59.687
My mom's in there.
We have to go back.

18:02.255 --> 18:03.343
- I was afraid
you would say that.

18:07.825 --> 18:07.999
.

18:08.043 --> 18:10.132
- Four days ago,
the world witnessed

18:10.176 --> 18:12.743
an unprecedented
natural disaster.

18:12.787 --> 18:15.094
The events at La Brea
have left Los Angeles

18:15.137 --> 18:16.747
in a state of mourning

18:16.791 --> 18:19.228
along with
unspeakable destruction.

18:19.272 --> 18:23.189
- All those people,
they don't even know the truth.

18:25.626 --> 18:27.018
It's not right.

18:27.062 --> 18:28.977
- That's why what we're doing
is so important.

18:29.020 --> 18:32.198
- Come over here
and take a look at this.

18:32.241 --> 18:34.591
I've mapped a low altitude
flight plan.

18:34.635 --> 18:36.985
The plane should be able to
avoid detection until La Brea,

18:37.028 --> 18:39.161
which, of course,
will be heavily monitored.

18:39.205 --> 18:43.252
But if Sophia does her job,
we'll be just fine.

18:43.296 --> 18:45.820
- And if she doesn't?

18:45.863 --> 18:47.996
- The truth?

18:48.039 --> 18:50.825
The plane will likely
be shot down.

18:50.868 --> 18:53.262
- That's not gonna happen.

18:53.306 --> 18:54.829
- Look, Izzy.

18:54.872 --> 18:56.178
I understand
that you're anxious.

18:56.222 --> 18:59.964
I would be too
if I were in your position,

19:00.008 --> 19:01.836
but there's no other way.

19:01.879 --> 19:03.098
- That's easy for you to say.

19:03.142 --> 19:05.622
You're not the one
in the plane.

19:05.666 --> 19:07.885
- That's not entirely accurate.

19:07.929 --> 19:09.887
[apprehensive music]

19:09.931 --> 19:12.542
I am going down there too.

19:14.849 --> 19:16.198
My friends are
stuck down there.

19:16.242 --> 19:19.941
It happened on my watch.
I have to bring them home.

19:19.984 --> 19:24.032
- Iz, if you tell me not to go,
I won't.

19:24.075 --> 19:27.905
- But if I say no, we'll never
see them again, will we?

19:31.822 --> 19:33.737
I'm sorry. I need to be alone.

19:33.781 --> 19:40.788
♪

19:45.053 --> 19:50.101
- Iz, I know you're upset,
but we need to talk.

19:53.148 --> 19:54.889
- I don't trust her.

19:54.932 --> 19:56.456
We have known her
all of two hours,

19:56.499 --> 19:58.762
and now she wants you to fly
into the sinkhole with her?

19:58.806 --> 19:59.937
- I understand,

19:59.981 --> 20:02.679
but I don't know
what else to do.

20:02.723 --> 20:05.247
- Let's say everything
Aldridge is saying is true,

20:05.291 --> 20:07.380
that a plane can
make it down there.

20:07.423 --> 20:10.818
What happens if you get
a vision while you're flying?

20:10.861 --> 20:11.862
- Iz...

20:13.342 --> 20:14.343
It'll be okay.

20:16.258 --> 20:17.912
- Dad, I'm scared.

20:19.218 --> 20:20.654
- I know.

20:22.960 --> 20:25.920
[indistinct voices]

20:25.963 --> 20:28.662
[suspenseful music]

20:28.705 --> 20:29.837
- Here.

20:29.880 --> 20:31.360
You take this
and use it if you need to.

20:31.404 --> 20:34.972
- Levi--
- Hey, you got this. Okay?

20:35.016 --> 20:37.366
Okay. Okay.

20:41.457 --> 20:43.111
Shh.

20:43.154 --> 20:50.161
♪

20:52.120 --> 20:53.426
- We just need to distract them

20:53.469 --> 20:55.950
so we can sneak back in
and get everyone out.

20:55.993 --> 20:57.647
- Okay, I guess
we'll just show them

20:57.691 --> 20:59.736
the new Billie Eilish video
on my phone?

20:59.780 --> 21:02.739
- This isn't a joke, Riley.
My mom and Levi are in there.

21:02.783 --> 21:04.001
So are Scott and Lucas.

21:04.045 --> 21:05.829
- They could've
gotten out by now.

21:05.873 --> 21:07.875
I'm not gonna go get myself
killed by going back in there.

21:07.918 --> 21:11.052
- So that's it?
You're just gonna leave?

21:11.095 --> 21:13.272
- What do you want from me?

21:13.315 --> 21:15.317
- You're such a hypocrite,
you know that?

21:15.361 --> 21:16.753
- Excuse me?

21:16.797 --> 21:17.798
- You were so pissed at my mom

21:17.841 --> 21:19.147
for not going back
for your dad.

21:19.190 --> 21:22.803
Now the roles are reversed.
You want to run?

21:22.846 --> 21:25.371
- This isn't the same thing.
- You're right.

21:25.414 --> 21:28.983
It's worse.
My mom was trying to help me.

21:29.026 --> 21:31.377
The only person you care about
is yourself.

21:34.380 --> 21:37.208
Look, I never took you

21:37.252 --> 21:39.994
as someone
who was scared of anything.

21:40.037 --> 21:42.953
You operated on your dad,
and you saved his life.

21:44.172 --> 21:46.130
That's who I need right now.

21:46.174 --> 21:52.180
♪

21:52.223 --> 21:58.012
- Okay. I'm in. What do we do?

21:59.492 --> 22:00.841
- Give me your phone.

22:00.884 --> 22:02.973
- Why?

22:03.017 --> 22:04.845
- I got an idea.

22:08.892 --> 22:11.373
- The intruders,
have you seen them?

22:14.855 --> 22:16.378
- We haven't seen anyone.

22:25.126 --> 22:26.954
- It's okay. They're gone.

22:29.260 --> 22:31.872
- Thank you. You speak English?

22:31.915 --> 22:35.832
- Yes, we all do.
You're the sky people.

22:35.876 --> 22:37.051
- What?

22:37.094 --> 22:38.966
- My grandfather told me
about you.

22:39.009 --> 22:41.751
You fell from that light
in the sky.

22:41.795 --> 22:43.362
Have you come to take
our village from us?

22:43.405 --> 22:44.841
- No. No, not at all.

22:44.885 --> 22:46.843
- You have to tell your
grandfather we mean no harm.

22:46.887 --> 22:50.499
- He's not here, but I don't
think he would believe you.

22:50.543 --> 22:53.850
- Hey, my son is on
the other side of that wall,

22:53.894 --> 22:55.417
and I need to get to him.

22:55.461 --> 22:57.550
Is there another way out?

22:57.593 --> 23:00.030
- Yes.
- Can you show us?

23:02.946 --> 23:04.383
- Come with me.

23:09.866 --> 23:10.258
.

23:10.301 --> 23:11.955
- That was a great
catch out there.

23:11.999 --> 23:13.174
- Thanks.

23:13.217 --> 23:15.742
- No, seriously.
You're a proper player.

23:15.785 --> 23:17.004
- My dad taught me.

23:17.047 --> 23:19.354
He used to coach
my softball team.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.356
We used to practice
in our backyard every day.

23:21.400 --> 23:22.836
- Really?

23:22.879 --> 23:24.359
The way Veronica
described your father,

23:24.403 --> 23:26.840
I didn't picture him
as a softball coach.

23:26.883 --> 23:29.843
[apprehensive music]

23:29.886 --> 23:32.759
♪

23:32.802 --> 23:34.413
Lilly, are you okay?

23:38.112 --> 23:39.983
Hey.

23:40.027 --> 23:41.724
If there's something
you want to say,

23:41.768 --> 23:43.770
you can tell me.

23:43.813 --> 23:46.642
Look, I'm your friend here.
You can trust me.

23:49.123 --> 23:51.691
- I'm sorry.
I don't want to play anymore.

23:59.438 --> 24:02.353
- I don't know what's going on.
Something's not right.

24:05.487 --> 24:07.446
- You know, I've thought of
every possible way

24:07.489 --> 24:08.925
things were going to end
for me.

24:08.969 --> 24:13.364
Cancer, heart attack,
brain aneurysm, plane crash...

24:13.408 --> 24:15.932
- Oh, my God.
- Accidental stabbing.

24:15.976 --> 24:18.326
But I gotta say, being killed
in a mysterious fort

24:18.369 --> 24:20.720
in 10,000 B.C.
just never crossed my mind.

24:20.763 --> 24:22.548
- Hey, hey.
Can you stop talking?

24:22.591 --> 24:23.766
- Actually, you know what,
in situations

24:23.810 --> 24:24.898
like this, I can't, okay?
It's a problem.

24:24.941 --> 24:26.029
- Hey, listen, listen.
- What?

24:26.073 --> 24:27.553
- I need you to slide
over here,

24:27.596 --> 24:30.643
Reach into my pocket.

24:30.686 --> 24:31.774
- Why?

24:31.818 --> 24:33.428
- There's a lighter
in there, okay?

24:33.472 --> 24:35.691
We can burn through the ropes
and free ourselves.

24:35.735 --> 24:37.345
- Wha--oh.

24:37.388 --> 24:39.347
Like in "Indiana Jones
and the Last Crusade."

24:39.390 --> 24:41.480
Nice.

24:41.523 --> 24:42.785
- What?

24:42.829 --> 24:43.960
- Never mind.

24:44.004 --> 24:47.573
[tense music]

24:47.616 --> 24:49.139
Ah. Okay, I got it.

24:49.183 --> 24:50.706
- You got it?
- I got it.

24:54.188 --> 24:55.450
- [grunts]
- Okay.

24:55.494 --> 24:57.670
[lighter clicking]

25:01.761 --> 25:03.110
[groans]

25:06.679 --> 25:08.115
Holy crap, it worked.

25:08.158 --> 25:11.118
- Oh, good, okay. Do me. Do me.

25:11.161 --> 25:12.772
- Yes. Shh. Okay.

25:16.602 --> 25:18.908
Actually.

25:18.952 --> 25:21.041
- What are you doing? Untie me.

25:23.434 --> 25:24.523
- Just promise me
if we get out of here,

25:24.566 --> 25:25.828
you're not gonna kill me.

25:25.872 --> 25:27.656
- Are you kidding me?

25:29.702 --> 25:31.486
You're bargaining with me now?

25:31.530 --> 25:33.836
- Well. Yeah.

25:33.880 --> 25:35.490
- Uh-uh. Nah. No deal.
- What?

25:35.534 --> 25:37.144
- What do you mean, no deal?!

25:37.187 --> 25:38.754
- You walk out of here
without me,

25:38.798 --> 25:40.539
you're not going
to make it two feet.

25:42.976 --> 25:45.456
- Damn it.
- Come on.

25:48.024 --> 25:50.636
Oh, man.
- Okay.

25:53.900 --> 25:55.162
Yeah, okay.

25:56.903 --> 25:59.775
- Ow! That hurt.
That really hurt.

25:59.819 --> 26:02.082
- Good. Now let's go.

26:05.912 --> 26:07.783
- It's just up here.

26:07.827 --> 26:14.834
♪

26:20.056 --> 26:21.536
- Who is that?

26:21.580 --> 26:23.059
- It's my grandfather.

26:23.103 --> 26:25.584
We need to hurry. Come on.

26:36.943 --> 26:39.902
[pop music playing
indistinctly]

26:39.946 --> 26:46.953
♪

26:51.131 --> 26:52.654
- Go, go.

27:03.796 --> 27:06.059
- Hey, Josh, Riley.

27:06.102 --> 27:07.538
- Where have you been?

27:07.582 --> 27:08.844
- Oh, you know, just having
a near-death experience.

27:08.888 --> 27:10.672
- Hey, hey, hey.
Everybody, shut up.

27:10.716 --> 27:11.934
We need to get out of here.

27:11.978 --> 27:13.240
- My mom and Levi
are still here.

27:13.283 --> 27:14.720
We can't leave without them.

27:14.763 --> 27:15.982
- Yeah, that sounds like
you problem, man.

27:16.025 --> 27:18.071
- You go by yourself,
you'll get killed.

27:18.114 --> 27:19.289
- Huh?

27:19.333 --> 27:20.508
We have a better chance
of staying alive

27:20.551 --> 27:22.902
if we stick together.

27:22.945 --> 27:24.164
Let's move.

27:28.081 --> 27:29.909
- Ah, come on.

27:40.920 --> 27:41.921
- Sophia.

27:43.357 --> 27:45.881
Thought you were
taking the day?

27:45.925 --> 27:48.101
- I just came to get
some things from the office.

27:48.144 --> 27:49.624
- Well, there may be
a few things missing.

27:49.668 --> 27:52.018
Gavin Harris stole his file.

27:52.061 --> 27:54.673
- Why would he do that?
- I don't know.

27:54.716 --> 27:56.805
Whatever he's planning,
it's not gonna work.

27:56.849 --> 27:58.851
I've doubled security
around the sinkhole.

28:00.679 --> 28:02.071
- Smart move.

28:04.204 --> 28:05.684
- Of course,
it won't be necessary

28:05.727 --> 28:08.948
if you tell me where he is.

28:10.645 --> 28:13.604
I know how badly you want to
get down there to find Diana,

28:13.648 --> 28:15.563
but there are other people
to consider.

28:15.606 --> 28:18.348
- Yeah, there are.
Like Gavin's family.

28:18.392 --> 28:20.829
Like the dozens of people
who fell in that sinkhole.

28:20.873 --> 28:23.571
- Don't you think I would
help them if I could?

28:25.181 --> 28:27.183
That earthquake was a 5.0.

28:27.227 --> 28:29.272
Our people predicted any other
disturbance in the sinkhole

28:29.316 --> 28:31.753
could cause
a catastrophic event.

28:31.797 --> 28:33.189
- You don't know that.

28:33.233 --> 28:36.323
- I'm not willing to risk it.

28:36.366 --> 28:39.326
Sophia, please, if you know
something, you have to tell me.

28:39.369 --> 28:42.721
[apprehensive music]

28:44.723 --> 28:47.943
- Gavin, I can't get
ahold of Sophia.

28:47.987 --> 28:50.250
- So we don't know
if she got the radar down?

28:50.293 --> 28:51.947
- No, but it doesn't
change anything.

28:51.991 --> 28:53.166
We still have to fly.

28:53.209 --> 28:54.167
- But you said it yourself.

28:54.210 --> 28:55.734
They'll shoot you down.

28:55.777 --> 28:58.040
Please, you can't do this.

28:58.084 --> 28:59.650
- She's right.

28:59.694 --> 29:02.349
We can't go anywhere
until we know it's safe.

29:03.742 --> 29:06.222
- I hate to be blunt,
but if we don't leave tonight,

29:06.266 --> 29:08.007
you'll never see
your family again.

29:09.922 --> 29:12.315
- Okay, what aren't you
telling us?

29:12.359 --> 29:16.885
Because if you want me to fly,
you have to tell us the truth.

29:20.759 --> 29:23.370
- There's something
I need to show you.

29:23.413 --> 29:28.070
It'll explain everything.
But it's not here. It's in LA.

29:28.114 --> 29:31.813
- You want us to drive back
to LA to show us something?

29:31.857 --> 29:33.249
- Oh, who said anything
about driving?

29:33.293 --> 29:40.126
♪

29:45.696 --> 29:47.350
[tense music]

29:47.394 --> 29:49.265
- Over there.

29:49.309 --> 29:51.398
- Those rocks,
they pull away from the wall.

29:51.441 --> 29:53.922
- Mom!

29:53.966 --> 29:56.359
- Josh. Thank God you're okay.

29:59.058 --> 30:00.059
- Go.
- Okay.

30:00.102 --> 30:02.278
- Let's go. Come on.

30:02.322 --> 30:03.323
Come on.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.197
- Eve go.
- There they are.

30:08.241 --> 30:14.900
♪

30:17.337 --> 30:17.511
.

30:17.554 --> 30:21.776
[tense music]

30:21.820 --> 30:22.821
- Stop.

30:29.175 --> 30:30.829
Let them go, Silas.

30:33.744 --> 30:37.836
- Go.
- Thank you.

30:37.879 --> 30:38.837
- Go.

30:38.880 --> 30:44.625
♪

30:44.668 --> 30:46.540
- Okay, not to state
the obvious,

30:46.583 --> 30:49.195
but Europeans didn't show up
and start colonizing this place

30:49.238 --> 30:50.326
until the 16th century.

30:50.370 --> 30:52.241
Those people shouldn't be here.

30:52.285 --> 30:53.503
- We're here.

30:53.547 --> 30:54.853
- Yeah, but they
didn't just arrive.

30:54.896 --> 30:56.767
It's like they'd been
living there for years.

30:56.811 --> 30:58.552
- Whoever they are,

30:58.595 --> 31:00.249
definitely
don't like outsiders.

31:00.293 --> 31:02.599
- Would you like it if people
broke into your house?

31:02.643 --> 31:03.644
- Hey.

31:06.342 --> 31:07.866
- What's up?

31:07.909 --> 31:10.651
- Soon as we get back, we go
looking for my stuff, okay?

31:10.694 --> 31:13.262
- I'm really sorry, man.
I don't remember where it is.

31:13.306 --> 31:14.568
- Then you got a big problem.

31:14.611 --> 31:16.657
- Do you not recall
what happened back there?

31:16.700 --> 31:18.267
I saved your life.

31:18.311 --> 31:20.835
- That doesn't make us even.

31:20.879 --> 31:22.924
- You know what?
You really want to kill me?

31:22.968 --> 31:25.796
Go for it. I'm serious.

31:25.840 --> 31:27.363
Just get it over and done with

31:27.407 --> 31:29.365
'cause I'm sick of being
your little bitch.

31:33.892 --> 31:36.546
- [laughs]

31:36.590 --> 31:40.376
Wow. Look at you, man.

31:40.420 --> 31:42.378
You finally grew a pair.

31:42.422 --> 31:43.989
[tense music]

31:44.032 --> 31:45.686
But you should have
left me tied up.

31:45.729 --> 31:52.736
♪

31:58.394 --> 31:59.787
- Yeah, this was fun.

31:59.830 --> 32:02.659
I didn't think about dying
for at least 20 minutes.

32:04.574 --> 32:07.882
- Riley!
- Dad.

32:09.623 --> 32:11.364
- we were getting so worried
about your guys.

32:17.065 --> 32:20.677
- You're the pilot?
- Captain Levi Delgado.

32:20.721 --> 32:21.983
It's a pleasure
to meet you all.

32:22.027 --> 32:24.464
- You're here to bring us home?

32:24.507 --> 32:25.900
- That was the plan.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.597
But unfortunately
my plane's damaged.

32:27.641 --> 32:30.818
I lost an engine.

32:30.861 --> 32:32.341
I wish I had better news.

32:32.385 --> 32:34.735
- So that's it.
We're stuck here.

32:34.778 --> 32:36.258
- I didn't say that.

32:36.302 --> 32:37.303
I came here to bring you home,

32:37.346 --> 32:39.392
and that's what
I'm going to do.

32:39.435 --> 32:41.307
However long it takes.

32:48.923 --> 32:52.709
- Hey, mind if I join?

32:52.753 --> 32:54.320
- Take a seat.

32:58.759 --> 32:59.803
You okay?

33:01.414 --> 33:03.720
- Yeah, I, uh,

33:03.764 --> 33:07.942
I just heard
about that guy who died, Eddie.

33:07.986 --> 33:10.031
They think that old man at
the fort might have killed him.

33:10.075 --> 33:12.555
- Yeah, I know.

33:16.342 --> 33:19.388
- Listen, I wanted to say
thank you

33:19.432 --> 33:21.912
for keeping me alive
out there and all.

33:21.956 --> 33:23.653
[soft heartfelt music]

33:23.697 --> 33:26.656
- Not bad for a guy a life
stage apart from you, huh?

33:26.700 --> 33:28.745
- [chuckles]

33:28.789 --> 33:31.357
- Yeah. Not bad.

33:31.400 --> 33:38.407
♪

33:42.498 --> 33:44.022
Good night, Josh.

33:52.813 --> 33:55.468
- Hey, Lilly.

33:55.511 --> 33:57.687
Why are you all by yourself?

33:57.731 --> 34:00.473
- Veronica went to get
some food.

34:00.516 --> 34:02.040
- May I?

34:13.399 --> 34:16.010
I'm sorry I upset you before.

34:16.054 --> 34:18.447
But if I'm being honest,

34:18.491 --> 34:20.841
I think you know more
than you're telling us

34:20.884 --> 34:23.974
about what happened to Eddie
and the man you saw.

34:24.018 --> 34:26.064
- I told you everything
I know about him.

34:26.107 --> 34:28.675
- Okay.
It's okay, I believe you.

34:30.894 --> 34:31.895
But Lilly...

34:33.593 --> 34:36.422
Is there something else
you want to say?

34:41.514 --> 34:43.907
Okay.

34:43.951 --> 34:48.564
Well, I'm here to help
if you ever need me.

34:55.571 --> 34:57.878
- Ty.

34:57.921 --> 35:00.533
- Yeah?

35:00.576 --> 35:01.925
- There is something else.

35:06.539 --> 35:07.888
- What is it?

35:11.196 --> 35:12.588
- Veronica?

35:15.243 --> 35:16.723
She's not my sister.

35:16.766 --> 35:19.726
[suspenseful music]

35:19.769 --> 35:23.730
♪

35:23.773 --> 35:26.776
- Lilly, what are you saying?

35:29.214 --> 35:30.563
- A year ago,

35:30.606 --> 35:33.435
I was with my family
at our church for a picnic.

35:34.958 --> 35:38.614
I went for a walk by myself,
and a car pulled up.

35:38.658 --> 35:41.748
It was Aaron and Veronica.

35:41.791 --> 35:43.010
They took me.

35:48.102 --> 35:52.019
- Oh, Lilly. It's okay.

36:01.855 --> 36:02.856
- Veronica.

36:08.818 --> 36:10.472
We need to talk.

36:12.605 --> 36:15.216
Veronica. Veronica, wait!

36:15.260 --> 36:21.918
♪

36:24.182 --> 36:25.618
- This is Captain Levi Delgado.

36:25.661 --> 36:27.620
If you can hear me,
please respond.

36:27.663 --> 36:29.622
[static crackles]

36:29.665 --> 36:31.798
[feedback whirring]

36:31.841 --> 36:33.103
This is Captain Levi Delgado.

36:33.147 --> 36:34.670
If you can hear me,
we need your help.

36:34.714 --> 36:36.150
Please respond.

36:36.194 --> 36:37.586
- You really think whoever's
on the other end of that

36:37.630 --> 36:39.197
can help us fix your plane?

36:41.851 --> 36:42.896
- They flew here.

36:42.939 --> 36:44.289
Maybe they have
parts we can use.

36:44.332 --> 36:46.247
Who knows, maybe their plane
can still fly.

36:46.291 --> 36:48.815
I think we can make it.

36:48.858 --> 36:52.993
- Hey, Levi, we need to talk.

36:53.036 --> 36:54.603
- Let me know the minute
you hear something.

36:54.647 --> 36:55.996
- Will do.

36:59.217 --> 37:01.871
Listen, I should have told you
the truth about my mission.

37:01.915 --> 37:04.047
I'm sorry.
- It's not about that.

37:07.137 --> 37:09.618
- You want to talk about Gavin?
- Yeah.

37:12.882 --> 37:14.884
I just--
I keep thinking about...

37:17.104 --> 37:20.107
How he must have felt
when he found out.

37:20.150 --> 37:22.152
How hurt he must've been.

37:23.937 --> 37:24.894
- Eve.

37:24.938 --> 37:27.941
[soft heartfelt music]

37:29.072 --> 37:32.119
- He wasn't there for you.

37:32.162 --> 37:34.643
You don't need to beat
yourself up over this.

37:34.687 --> 37:36.079
- I can't help it.

37:40.693 --> 37:42.085
What did he say
when you told him?

37:42.129 --> 37:44.610
- Eve, I don't--
- I just--I need to know.

37:50.703 --> 37:52.574
- He asked me if I loved you.

37:54.359 --> 37:55.316
- What did you say?

37:57.927 --> 37:59.625
- I didn't
have to say anything.

38:01.279 --> 38:02.715
He knew the answer.

38:02.758 --> 38:09.765
♪

38:13.769 --> 38:16.119
- I'm going to get some rest.

38:17.425 --> 38:18.818
- Okay.

38:28.828 --> 38:31.918
[suspenseful music]

38:31.961 --> 38:36.749
♪

38:36.792 --> 38:38.359
[keypad beeping]

38:38.403 --> 38:39.882
[buzzer blares]

38:39.926 --> 38:41.101
- Follow me.

38:46.802 --> 38:49.762
- You brought us here
to see a construction site.

38:49.805 --> 38:56.812
♪

39:02.427 --> 39:03.950
- What is this place?

39:03.993 --> 39:05.299
- This is where the survivors

39:05.343 --> 39:07.823
of the La Brea sinkhole
settled in 10,000 BC.

39:11.261 --> 39:12.741
- How did you find it?

39:12.785 --> 39:15.788
- All you need to know
is why you're here.

39:15.831 --> 39:19.313
We found something from Eve.

39:28.104 --> 39:30.063
The interesting thing
about glass

39:30.106 --> 39:34.241
is that it takes almost
a million years to decompose.

39:34.284 --> 39:37.853
In this particular bottle,
we found something.

39:37.897 --> 39:39.768
A letter.

39:39.812 --> 39:42.423
- From my mom?
- Yeah.

39:42.467 --> 39:45.426
- When my team found it,
the letter was in fragments,

39:45.470 --> 39:49.430
but they were able
to reconstruct it.

39:49.474 --> 39:56.394
♪

39:56.437 --> 39:59.832
- "Dear Gavin and Izzy,

39:59.875 --> 40:03.792
"I know this is
probably crazy and hopeless.

40:03.836 --> 40:06.795
"But somehow you found my ring.

40:06.839 --> 40:12.279
Maybe if there's a miracle,
you'll find this letter."

40:12.322 --> 40:15.108
- I've been down here
five nights

40:15.151 --> 40:16.892
holding onto the hope
that Josh and I

40:16.936 --> 40:18.894
would find our way back
to you both.

40:21.244 --> 40:22.855
But now something's happened.

40:22.898 --> 40:26.902
♪

40:26.946 --> 40:28.730
Tonight,

40:28.774 --> 40:32.995
the light that connects
our worlds started to close.

40:40.916 --> 40:42.265
- Five nights.

40:44.442 --> 40:46.792
That's tonight.

40:46.835 --> 40:48.794
- Gavin, I wish
we had more time

40:48.837 --> 40:52.188
to try and fix everything
that got broken between us.

40:52.232 --> 40:53.842
Just know that in my heart,

40:53.886 --> 40:57.193
I am so sorry
for doubting you.

40:57.237 --> 41:00.240
I should have
believed you all along.

41:00.283 --> 41:03.417
- "Izzy, my strong
and beautiful daughter,

41:03.461 --> 41:06.855
"you have your whole life
to look forward to.

41:06.899 --> 41:09.249
Lean on your father
and take care of each other."

41:09.292 --> 41:12.861
[sentimental music]

41:12.905 --> 41:15.124
- Gavin, I don't know
if or when I'll ever

41:15.168 --> 41:16.909
see either one of you again,
but I know

41:16.952 --> 41:20.129
if there's some way,
any way, to help us,

41:20.173 --> 41:23.089
that you'll find it.

41:23.132 --> 41:25.787
Wherever you are,
wherever I am,

41:25.831 --> 41:26.788
no matter what...

41:26.832 --> 41:28.921
[sighs]

41:28.964 --> 41:30.488
You're always with me.

41:32.925 --> 41:35.493
- "All my love, Eve."

41:40.323 --> 41:41.934
The light's closing.

41:41.977 --> 41:43.936
Why the hell
didn't you tell me?

41:43.979 --> 41:45.241
- Because once
we get down there,

41:45.285 --> 41:47.592
I can't guarantee
you'll make it back.

41:47.635 --> 41:50.420
- And you knew he'd never
leave me if you told us that.

41:50.464 --> 41:51.596
- Yeah.

41:51.639 --> 41:55.164
- So why tell me now?
- I had no choice.

41:55.208 --> 41:58.037
By this time tomorrow,
the light will be gone.

41:58.080 --> 41:59.429
If you want to save them,

41:59.473 --> 42:01.170
you're gonna
have to take the risk.

42:01.214 --> 42:04.173
[suspenseful music]

42:04.217 --> 42:06.262
♪

42:06.306 --> 42:08.177
- I can't do that.

42:08.221 --> 42:09.309
- But if you don't,

42:09.352 --> 42:10.919
we'll never get Mom
and Josh back.

42:10.963 --> 42:13.226
- Iz--
- I'll be fine, okay?

42:13.269 --> 42:15.533
I have Aunt Jessica.

42:15.576 --> 42:18.579
Please go save them.

42:18.623 --> 42:20.276
You have to.

42:20.320 --> 42:22.844
♪

42:25.020 --> 42:27.980
[dramatic music]

42:28.023 --> 42:35.030
♪
